data.value: The Neviastata Ecopath is located near Smolyan, in the Rhodope Mountains. It starts from the fork to the monastery of St. Panteleymon. It leads to the eponymous rock, which is one of the symbols of the city. There is an artificial climbing wall, alpine trolley, rock climbing routes, benches and tables, arbors, playgrounds and more.
